I just want to thank each and every legislator who has been working hard and giving their time to end this opioid abuse epidemic.
It's not one action that is going to solve this opioid abuse epidemic, we need to look at the whole system to find ways to improve it.
"If we have a shot at [ending this epidemic], we need to get the general public to get engaged. We can win this thing." - Mike Hirst
"We are all being affected by [opioid abuse] in one way or another, we have to educate we have to talk about this." - @andyschor
"Prescription drug and opioid abuse is not a partisan issue, it's not a republican or a democrat issue." - @andyschor
"I'm pleased with how much we've already accomplished because of work legislators have done, but we still have a long way to go." - Judge D.
"We have to change the culture of what American people think. We need to change the stigma that goes with addiction." -Judge Davis
"This is a problem that is more than just a death toll, it is affecting each & everyone of us every day." - Judge Davis
"We should make sure we are doing everything that we can to save lives, we want to have more second chances and less funerals" @LtGovCalley
We need to support each other, and ultimately come together to stop this epidemic.
We've done a lot of good things to combat opioid abuse, but to be blunt, we need to do more.
I want to compliment our judicial system in terms of what we've done with drug treatment courts.
In terms of opioid abuse we've done some great things, but we need to work harder.
I think we did good work with the Good Samaritan law that was put into place, but we need continue to work hard to combat this problem.
I appreciate having representatives from law enforcement here to discuss the work we're doing to combat this opioid problem.
We need to be a leader here in MI in terms of fighting this opioid abuse epidemic.

BL: I believe these recommendations do well to support Mi’s rural communities, and ensure that residents have an improved quality of life.
BL: We should establish the Michigan Consortium on Advanced Networks, developing a roadmap to enact a digital transformation of Michigan
BL: We listened to concerns and understand the importance of ensuring all Michiganders have access to broadband services. #MIInfrastructure
BL: lack of access to broadband, especially in rural areas, means communities aren't able to attract mobile talent and grow their economies.
Ben LaCross: Nearly half a million households in Michigan are without access to advanced broadband. #MIInfrastructure
The full report will be available at 10 a.m #MIinfrastructure
BW: We know that our transportation systems need to be improved we can’t just focus on fixing them today. We also need to look to the future
BW: With improved road conditions and intelligent vehicle technology, Michigan can achieve our goal of zero deaths on Michigan’s roads.
BW: We must invest in our roads and bridges to ensure they are in good or fair condition and safer and more reliable. #MIinfrastructure
Beverly Watts: For more than 1/2 century we’ve ignored the challenges facing our transportation systems and the results speak for themselves
EP:Our recommendations will help communities across our state achieve reliable affordable and safe infrastructure systems #MiInfrastructure
EP: MI's water systems are aging and we need to act with urgency to ensure our water systems are safe and reliable. #MIinfrastructure
EP: Securing our assets will be especially important as we move through the 21st century. #MIInfrastructure
EP: All agencies need to work together to establish goals so we can all see the positive results of renewed investment. #MIInfrastructure
Evan Pratt: We must find a better way to coordinate, assess, and improve the dire condition of all of our assets. #MiInfrastructure
HT: we need to ensure that our infrastructure is ready to meet the realities of emerging technologies in the 21st century.
HT: fixing our infrastructure for today is only the first step. This plan is about MI’s future. #MiInfrastructure
HT: You can view the full report on Commission’s website: https://t.co/QEw6NYbDG0.
Helen Taylor: As a Commission, we were tasked with developing a long-term and bold vision for infrastructure systems #MiInfrastructure
E.W: We need to invest in our roads and bridges to make sure they’re in good or fair condition, not just today, but for the future.
E.W: The Commission recommends that we need to invest in the replacement of our aging water, sewer, and stormwater infrastructure
E.W: this report is not a funding package -we’ve outlined the investment needs over the next 20 yrs and offered a menu of options.
Evan Weiner: we wanted to create infrastructure systems across the state to help enhance the quality of life for all Mi residents.
